Basic knowledges about aspects of immune system are given. Also we explain how to evaluate  immune system function and treatment in clinical settings.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To get basic knowledges for the further studies in dentistry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course, within the syllabus, a student:  1. is acquainted with the basic but up-to-date knowledge about the immune system; 2. knows and understands the cellular and molecular mechanisms of the immune system; 3. knows the basic properties of the diseases and conditions which are immune system related, is able to understand the corresponding immune processes in the human organism, has deepened understanding about these processes in stomatology; 4. knows how to evaluate the status of the immune system and corresponding options for immune modulation, knows immunological methods and their use in diagnosis; 5. is able to navigate in the modern medical literature on the field of immunology, is able to find specialized scientific articles.
